* ============================================================
*  TABLE-BUFFER WAL — PHASE C: DELETE routed through the buffer/log
*
*  Status:  CANDIDATE / REVIEW_BEFORE_EXECUTION. MUTATING (throwaway table).
*  Purpose: With TABLE BUFFER on, DELETE stages a CHANGE_DELETE + journals a D
*           redo record and defers the DBF mutation to COMMIT (or discards on
*           ROLLBACK) -- so deletes are transactional like REPLACE. The default
*           (buffer-off) DELETE keeps its write-through + batched-index path.
*           WALDEL has no CDX index, so this isolates the transactional behavior
*           from the separate buffered-commit-vs-CDX-index reconciliation caveat.
*
*  RUN (host):
*    powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\dottalkpp\data\scripts\pinocchio\run_wal_phaseC_proof_teed.ps1
* ============================================================
SET ECHO OFF
SET TIMER ON
SET TALK ON

SET PATH DBF DBF/pinocchio

CLOSE
ERASE TABLE WALDEL CONFIRM
CREATE X64 WALDEL (ID N(4), NAME C(20))
APPEND
REPLACE ID WITH "1"
REPLACE NAME WITH "Alpha"
APPEND
REPLACE ID WITH "2"
REPLACE NAME WITH "Beta"
APPEND
REPLACE ID WITH "3"
REPLACE NAME WITH "Gamma"
COUNT

TABLE BUFFER ON PERSISTENT

ECHO === C1. buffered DELETE recno 2 -- deferred until COMMIT ===
GO 2
DELETE
ECHO --- before COMMIT: COUNT DELETED should be 0 (staged only, DBF untouched) ---
COUNT DELETED
COMMIT
ECHO --- after COMMIT: COUNT DELETED should be 1 (recno 2 delete applied) ---
COUNT DELETED

ECHO === C2. buffered DELETE recno 3 then ROLLBACK -- discarded ===
GO 3
DELETE
ROLLBACK
ECHO --- after ROLLBACK: COUNT DELETED should still be 1 (recno 3 delete discarded) ---
COUNT DELETED
GO 3
ECHO --- recno 3 should NOT be deleted ---
DISPLAY

ECHO === C3. cleanup ===
TABLE BUFFER OFF
CLOSE
ERASE TABLE WALDEL CONFIRM

ECHO ============================================================
ECHO WAL PHASE C PROOF COMPLETE. Confirm:
ECHO   C1: COUNT DELETED = 0 before COMMIT, = 1 after (buffered delete applied on commit).
ECHO   C2: COUNT DELETED = 1 after ROLLBACK (recno 3 buffered delete discarded); recno 3 live.
ECHO ============================================================
